This article is about immigration reform and the framework laid out by the White House. It mentions that attempts at immigration reform have failed in the past due to the influence of open borders special interests in both parties. The article highlights three key points in the White House framework: securing the border, ending extended-family chain migration, and canceling the visa lottery. It also mentions that recent polling shows public support for a DACA fix that includes ending chain migration, eliminating the visa lottery, and securing the border.